If anything, SMB3 presents more problems a SMB1 hack wouldn't have, namely what freedom the other player has to move back through the level.  It might work by making the other player a slave like in Kirby Super Star, which transports the helper to Kirby's location.  If you insist on a split screen, the status bar will just have to go and the score can be visible on the map.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3506">strat</a> — Thu May 29, 2014 9:55 am</p><hr />
